args: Do you remember this place, Sheila?
I came here many times with you\nin the past, yes?
So you do remember. Good. Well then,\nwould you care to take a walk around?
My father and I came to a mountain town a short\nway from Lefkos to gather supplies for our travels.
I have memories of coming here with my father\nin the past—so after we gathered what we needed,\nwe decided to take a nostalgic stroll through town.
Ah, it was still under construction when we\ncame here last, wasn't it? Goodness, but it\nhas been some time!
Oh no! D-don't cry. Er...stop crying?\nOh dear. How do I help him?!
I'm so, SO sorry about my son!

Are you okay, Nico? There there, no more.
If you stop crying, I'll give you some candy!
You won't be able to eat it if you don't
stop crying!
I'm so sorry to trouble you both with...\nWait. Lady Sheila?!
But it's been over a decade since I last\nsaw you and you look exactly the same!\nHow is that possible?
And King Gatov! Oh, I haven't seen you\nin so long! It's me! Ignacio!
So I was right! I barely recognized you.\nI'm glad to see you in good health.
You seem to be doing well for yourself—\nbut never in my wildest dreams did I think\nto see you here!
Yes, my only child. His name is Nico.\nGo on, Nico! Say hello.
Quite the bundle of energy, isn't he?\nI recall when we first met at that party—\nyou were so timid compared to him.
That's also when you met Sheila, yes?
Your daughter helped me SO MUCH\nback then.
I was helping you...back then?\nI'm not sure I...
Ah, do you not remember? That's okay.\nIt was a long time ago, so I understand\nif you forgot about it.
I was having some real trouble, and you\nhelped me out over and over again.

You taught me how to dance when I had
two left feet, and you helped cover for me
when I accidentally knocked over an entire
table of food...
A bunch of kids were picking on me and\nI was too scared to say anything, but you\ncame running and saved the day.
Oh, I DO remember that now!
You never cared about social status—\nif you saw someone in trouble,\nyou'd help no matter what.

You were so elegant and refined, and yet
a ray of sunshine all the same—one that
was even willing to reach out and help a
wimpy commoner like me.
I'm sorry, Lady Sheila, but are you not\nfeeling well? You seem a bit...gloomier\nthan before.
Forgive us. During the fall of Lefkos...
...I had no idea. I too bore witness to the\nfall of the country, so I know all too well\nhow painful a thing it was.
I was so happy to see you both again that\nI failed to be as considerate as I should\nhave been. You have my sincere apologies.
That's not necessary. And while I'll spare\nyou the details, Sheila has regained her\nheart and is slowly on the mend.
That's good to hear. I want you to always\nbe the kind, strong person you were back\nwhen you were helping me out!
Daddy, don't we need to go?
Oh, right. We'd better get back home\nbefore your mom blows a gasket.\nShe can be a real terror when she's mad...
Apologies for having held you up.

I should be the one apologizing to you!
I'm no longer even a low-ranking noble,
yet I thought it acceptable to run over and 
start babbling to someone of your status.
Heh, we are no longer of lofty status\nourselves, so feel free to talk to us\nhowever you like from here on out.
Thank you so much! Now, we should go.\nI'll pray for your health, Lady Sheila.
We should be off as well.
(What is this feeling...?\nWhy does my heart hurt...?)

Phew! You've grown much more adept 
with that dagger. I'll have to be more
careful in these little training sessions,
lest you give me a scar to remember it by.
I know—but I fear the hours of constant\nsparring are too much for this old man.
That's not how you used to be.
That was a decade ago, Sheila—and most\nof us, no matter how strong, cannot wage\nwar against age and emerge victorious.

But you, my daughter? You are special.
Your body did not age while your heart
was gone, so you are still as full of energy
as you were at your prime.
Normally, a body grows weaker as the\nyears pass, and one finds themselves\neach day a little less adept than before.
Anyway, I was thinking about going back\ninto town. Would you care to join me?
Everything changed while I was\ncompletely unaware...
(My heart hurts... It hurt so much when\nwe talked to Ignacio yesterday, and then\nagain today while training with Father...)
Is there a reason you're staring\nat that church, Sheila?
In that case, let us be off.
(...I think I understand. I'm sad that so\nmuch has changed while I was unaware.)
So I won't change—I don't EVER\nwant to change.
But if everyone else is changing and I\ndon't...will they leave me behind?
